description: P3 Series. The 3 mm Microarray Breakout cable from Superior Essex is designed for high performance in a small package. The premises loose tube design consists of 3 mm microarray interconnect cable subunits, each of which contain either eight or twelve 250 micron fibers. The aramid yarns inside the subunit allow the subunit to be crimped directly onto an MTP®/MPO connector. The 3 mm subunits are stranded around a central strength element that is both flexible and robust enough to pass backbone installation requirements. The stranded subunits are held to the strength element core by binder yarns and/or tapes ensuring excellent temperature performance. Finally, a RoHS-compliant flexible jacket protects the core from the rigors of installation while providing riser or plenum fire protection. The cable is available with TeraFlex® single mode, and laser-optimized 50/125 micron 10G/150 (OM2+), 10G/300 (OM3) and 10G/550 (OM4) multimode fiber types.

description:
558GMS
Access Control

Access Control
Access Control cables contain multiple cables each designed for a specific application. These applications
include: card readers, door contacts, REX (request exit), and locking power.
Although each cable has a separate application and cable requirements, they are installed in the same vicinity.
Access Control cables are grouped together to make their installation easier. There are two main methods of
grouping the cables together: applying an overall jacket or applying a substrate between the cables to “stick”
them together (Banana Peel®). Jacketed versions (ex: AFJ) are generally larger than the Banana Peel
versions (ex: AFS) and are more difficult to install since the jacket needs to be removed.
The listed Access Control cables have four different cables grouped together. Each cable ranges from #16 to
#22 AWG and has 16 to 18 conductors. Insulations include polyolefin and/or PVC. Foil shields with drain
wires are used when necessary and the jackets/substrates are PVC or LSZH.
